#: ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:161 ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:161
msgid "A source has at least one access point, but may have many. For example, if a source is a document we may draw information from a number of different pages (or ranges of pages). For each page or range of pages, we would create a new access point to the source. The field :ref:`source:access_point_type` tells us what method we have used to create the access point - in this case ``page``. The number of the page or page range will be recorded in a related attribute called :ref:`source:access_point_trigger`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:163 ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:163
msgid "There are eight ways to "trigger" a citation of a specific source, taking in account the source's media type:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:165 ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:165
msgid "- ``archive``: an archive snapshot of the source."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:166 ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:166
msgid "- ``page``: a page or range of page in a document source like a book or report."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:167 ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:167
msgid "- ``line``: a line or range of lines in a line-numbered document like an interview transcript."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:168 ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:168
msgid "- ``clip``: a passage from a video or audio source, comprising a start time and a stop time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:169 ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:169
msgid "- ``frame``: a single capture point in a video."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:170 ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:170
msgid "- ``paragraph``: where a document is numbered throughout, such as in United Nations Security Council documents, paragraphs can be used as access point triggers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:171 ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:171
msgid "- ``cell``: the cell reference or range within a table of data"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:173 ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:173
msgid "As we seek to include different types of sources in our work, we anticipate updating this list of citation types."
msgstr ""

