#: ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:208 ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:208
msgid "This field is used to specify the exact content within a source that defines the citation. For example, if we want to create a citation of page 4 of a source then we would set the value in :ref:`source:access_point_type` to ``page`` and enter ``4`` in this attribute. As noted in the documentation for :ref:`source:access_point_type` there are seven ways to trigger a citation. These are listed below, along with the data type and format required to specify the exact content of the citation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:210 ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:210
msgid "- ``archive``: Leave empty. The value in :ref:`source:archive_url` serves as the trigger for this citation type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:211 ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:211
msgid "- ``page``: Single page (``1``), single range of pages (``1-2``), combination of page and page ranges (``1,2-3,4,5-8``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:212 ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:212
msgid "- ``line``: Single line (``200``), single range of lines (``200-230``), combination of line and line ranges (``200-230,236,240-250``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:213 ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:213
msgid "- ``clip``: Single range containing start and end time in the format ``hh:mm:ss`` (``00:01:20-00:01:24``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:214 ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:214
msgid "- ``frame``: A single capture point from a video in ``hh:mm:ss`` format (``00:01:20``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:214 ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:215
msgid "- ``paragraph``: if a document has numbered paragraphs in any format (e.g. ``3(1)(a)``), they can be captured here."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:214 ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:216
msgid "- ``cell``: the grid reference (``C123``) of the cell, or cell range (``C123-C129``), containing the data used to evidence the claim."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:218 ../../source/source-citation-specific.rst:218
msgid "The range of access point triggers may extend as different media forms become available."
msgstr ""

